metadata.name: Zhu(竹) #89
metadata.description:
Zhu(竹):

"Zhu" is a series of 100 oriental abstract pieces featuring the imagery of bamboo, a symbol of integrity and strength in traditional Chinese culture.

Zhu's generative system is an exploration of this cultural symbol by modern art language. Elements of the paintings are merely circles, enclosed flow field shapes, and the blank space behind these visual objects. Blank-leaving is intentionally applied at various degrees throughout the series. The vast empty space beyond the plants is open to and embraces every kind of interpretation.

Zhu's outputs span hours of the day from dawn to dusk to night. Its color schemes explored four styles from traditional to modern. The simple yet complex senses and feelings reflected are surprisingly versatile.

metadata.name: Chaos Culture #286
metadata.description:
"Chaos Culture" is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at The Ever-Evolving World of Art, Art Basel Hong-Kong, 2022.

《西遊記》第一回:「混沌未分天地亂，茫茫渺渺無人見。」

Chaos Culture is the final chapter of this series. There is a legend in the East that before Pan Gu opened up the sky and created the earth, the world was a chaotic place, and no one knew its appearance. And I have always been fascinated by this mythical story since he was a child.

These three works have a father-son relationship, Research > Memory > Culture, with each work re-growing through the remnants of the previous work, depending on its image. From the beginning of the creative coding, I like the concept of recursion the most. Here I experiment with my central thinking through this iterative relationship so that the work is not only the shadow of the artist but also the pulling force of repetition.

"混沌" Chaos in Eastern culture represents the initial state of things. This state is consistent with what we believe in generative art: Anything can happen if different forces are applied. Letting chaos grow out of order and then destroying it, the iterative process, is like my usual dialogue with myself, and maybe it's all just a diary.

Through these three series of works, whether I can eventually find everything in my childhood fantasy, I am not sure yet. The only thing I can be sure of is that I will continue to explore.

- Click the mouse to save an artwork.
- Collectors who own this NFT have the right to print the work.

Artist: Aluan Wang (ileivoivm).
Made with p5js and glsl.

metadata.name: Winesburg, Ohio #31
metadata.description: “Winesburg, Ohio” is an act of uncanny place-making. The collection borrows its name from a 1919 short-story cycle by Sherwood Anderson, which explores a peculiar cast of characters living within a fictionalized, midwestern town. Like Anderson’s text, the “Winesburg, Ohio” algorithm constructs a world through recurring portrayals of specific structures and landmarks. Its scenes are populated by a variety of familiar elements taken from my larger body of work, including water towers, houses, and churches. Meanwhile, a series of scripted gestures insert abstract compositional elements into the outputs, counteracting their pictorial legibility. The strange landscapes that result are composite ideograms, comprised of multiple spatial possibilities that co-exist in varying states of contradiction.

metadata.name: trāma #10
metadata.description:
trāma is part of the interactive minting experience at NFT Show Europe, Valencia, 2023.

++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

trāma is a project in continuity with a wider body of work exploring the subject of computers as a source of aesthetic phenomena.

Beyond being utilitarian machines, is it possible to have such devices not only as mediators between representational content and humans, but also as aesthetic manifestations that connect to our senses?

The low visual resolution, the motion, and the timing of the work are informed by early computer graphics, mechanical displays and the rawness that older computational systems tend to carry.

trāma features a generative system, conducted through realtime custom software that runs in the browser.


++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++


press [p] = pause the animation
press [s] = save a screenshot
press [g] = generate gif

metadata.name: MOMENT #237
metadata.description:
An endless row of them making up each life. Some poignant, some inspiring, some grievous, some affirming - but most of them a tad boring, a bit generic, almost forgettable like bland fabric. How can a life constructed from such mundanity count for anything? Maybe thanks to the last one, the one that stitches them all together, like a punchline to an absurdist joke.

Generative art written in JavaScript + Canvas with a little bit of help from p5.js.

metadata.name: Ataraxis #583
metadata.description:
Ataraxis (or a broken volume renderer) is an exploration in balancing discomfort and calm. The piece generates spaces on the fly that are designed to elicit strange and uncomfortable feelings - like a desolate, alien dreamscape - claustrophobic, surreal, not quite real yet strangely recognisable. But the idea is that while these spaces feel uncomfortable, they're also strangely, antilogically calming. The idea is to elicit a sanguine emotion, to make the viewer feel calm in a strange place, and to lead them somewhere else.

This work is the culmination of many years of work researching volumetric rendering techniques. This token uses a raymarching technique that is intentionally broken in various ways.

Controls:
Double-click to download
&w=X&h=y to change the size of the piece
&dpr=x to change the resolution of the pice - higher resolutions will result in slightly different artworks as the browser attempts to compensate for the overlarge canvas
&fullscreen=true to change the token to display the full size of your browser. This may impact the rendering of the token, so use with caution

metadata.name: CryptoPixels #100
metadata.description:
The ultimate collectible.
 
Traits? Well, each pixel has an R value, a G value, and a B value. And yeah, Tyler Hobbs, we know you’re reading and are about to say we should use H, S, and B instead but you can shove it up your ass right along with your Fidenza billions. Real deep up there.
 
Utility? With only 576 CryptoPixels you can make a CryptoPunk worth millions!
 
Rarity? Each pixel is provably unique (in the Heraclitean sense). And you know how one of your drunk crypto bros mentioned hashes once and it was the only word short enough for you to remember after blacking out? We give you 3 hashes. Think of the street cred with the even dumber fuckers out there buying random numbers!
 
Bullshit hidden messages? Oh yeah, you’re getting excited now, aren’t you? We’ve done some real alien shit and buried blueprints for a spaceship in here. You just have to work with the “community” to combine your pixels into the plans. Real. Fucking. Interstellar. Travel. How’s that roadmap?
 
Is this art? Are you art?

attributes.name: Backstory
attributes.value: Springing from the forehead of Zeus, this pixel lived as a lonely goddess until an old wizard called it to adventure and it decided to wage a battle to destroy the evil forces of the Decepticons.

metadata.name: Floating Point  #68
metadata.description:
'Floating Point' by pixelwank 

Inspired by pastel smudging and the aerial photography of Rich Caldwell, Floating Point has impressions of a landscape and other structures. 

Homage to floating point numbers and how just one decimal difference can change it all. 

Floating Point is also the fictional name of the place where this work takes me, where does it take you?

In live mode, click the image or press 's' or 'S' to save 3000x4000 png 

Thanks for collecting 
Shoutout Circolors for the support & frenship <3 

Made with p5js

metadata.name: Gravity's End #230
metadata.description:
Gravity's End depicts fictional worlds being warped, distorted, and in rare cases, shattered, due to extreme gravitational forces.

Gravity's End is written with shaders, so a gpu is recommended. It is very gpu friendly, in that only one frame is rendered.

Rarities

- 21 palettes with 5 rare palettes (4% chance for rare).
- 10% chance of getting a shattered world.

Keys: 

's' saves a png in the exact size of the screen.
